              </name>
                  <description>
                <lang xml:lang="en"></lang>
              </description>
      
                  <value from="00" to="00">
                <description>
                    <lang xml:lang="en">Enable flash mode wich operates as follows: With Parameter 104 value set to 0, relay is closed and ZRP100 defaults to ON (relay closed).
Whenever the ZRP100 receives a Z-Wave ON command, the ZRP100 will begin cycling its output
relay on and off approximate once per second (1/2 second Off, 1/2 second On) for 20 seconds.
If at any time during that 20 seconds, the ZRP100 receives a Z-Wave OFF command, the ZRP100
will stop cycling its output relay and default to ON.
At any time during that 20 seconds, if the ZRP100 receives a Z-Wave ON command, the ZRP100
will add an additional 20 seconds on/off cycling of its output relay. At the end of the 20 seconds,
the ZRP100 will again default to ON (relay closed).
At any other time, if the ZRP100 receives an OFF command, it will have no effect and the ZRP100
remains ON.</lang>
                  </description>
              </value>
            <value from="01" to="01">
                <description>
                    <lang xml:lang="en">Normal ON/OFF operation</lang>
                  </description>
              </value>
                </configParam>
